                                    <p>7.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; All members will hand over their choice of selected themes in the prescribed <strong> Proforma at Appendix A to JDS University Division by 13 Feb 2021. Allotment of theme for thesis topic will be put up on the Notice Board on 08 Mar 2021. </strong></p>
                                    <hr />
                                    <h3 class="text-primary"><strong>Outline</strong></h3>
                                    <p>8.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; An outline is to be prepared by each member <strong>prior to the preliminary discussion</strong> with their respective guides. <strong>The preliminary interaction with the guide will be from 22 Feb 2021 to 26 Feb 2021. This will be followed by the synopsis of the thesis and form the basis for all subsequent work.</strong></p>
                                    <hr />
                                    <h3 class="text-primary"><strong>Guide</strong></h3>
                                    <p>9.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; The thesis is to be prepared in consultation with the guide, who will be available for advice and discussion. The names of the guide will be notified along with the allotment of themes.</p>
                                    <hr />
                                    <h3 class="text-primary"><strong>Submission of Thesis</strong></h3>
                                    <p>10.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Timely submission of the thesis</strong> is the responsibility of each member. Computer facilities are available in the Library and Raksha Bhawan, which can be freely used. Any additional assistance necessary is to be sought through the respective guide.</p>
                                    <hr />
                                    <h3 class="text-primary"><strong>Stationerry</strong></h3>
                                    <p>11.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Standard size (A4) typing paper</strong> available in the College will be supplied for the final thesis. You are requested not to use any other size paper and are expected to make your arrangements for paper for additional manuscripts, drafts, etc.</p>
                                    <hr />
                                    <h3 class="text-primary"><strong>Time Schedule</strong></h3>
                                    <p>12.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; The schedule given below is followed to ensure timely submission of the thesis. Changes if any, will be intimated in a weekly training program issued by Training Section. All activities are to be with the allotted Guides: ‑</p>
